---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-taiwan', text: 'Leaving Taiwanese Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'nhi-considerations', text: 'NHI Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Asia Insurance', href: '/best/asia-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'usNetwork', header: 'US Network' },
  { key: 'globalNetwork', header: 'Global Network' },
  { key: 'taiwanCoverage', header: 'Taiwan Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', usNetwork: 'Strong', globalNetwork: 'Excellent', taiwanCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'TWD 5,500/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', usNetwork: 'Excellent', globalNetwork: 'Excellent', taiwanCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'TWD 6,200/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', usNetwork: 'Good', globalNetwork: 'Strong', taiwanCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'TWD 5,200/mo' },
  { provider: 'Cathay Life', usNetwork: 'Limited', globalNetwork: 'Limited', taiwanCoverage: 'Included', price: 'TWD 4,000/mo' },
  { provider: 'Fubon Insurance', usNetwork: 'Limited', globalNetwork: 'Limited', taiwanCoverage: 'Included', price: 'TWD 3,800/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Taiwanese Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Taiwanese expats. Find coverage for the US, Europe, and other destinations while understanding NHI implications."
  headline="Best Insurance for Taiwanese Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Taiwan has excellent healthcare through NHI. Here's how to stay covered when you work or study abroad—and understand your NHI options."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/taiwanese-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwanese expats are found in significant numbers in the US (especially tech workers), Japan, Europe, and other countries. Understanding how NHI works when abroad is important. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Taiwanese expats. Strong US networks (critical for tech workers), comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Top-tier service quality.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong European networks.</li>
    <li><strong>Cathay Life:</strong> Major Taiwanese insurer with international products. Familiar brand, includes Taiwan.</li>
    <li><strong>Fubon Insurance:</strong> Taiwanese insurer with some international options. Familiar service.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="US Tech Worker Coverage"
    description="Many Taiwanese expats work in US tech companies. Employer coverage is common but ends with employment. International insurance provides continuity during job transitions—critical in the volatile tech industry."
    buttonText="Get US Coverage Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-taiwan">Leaving Taiwanese Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan's National Health Insurance (NHI) is one of the world's best healthcare systems. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>NHI Coverage Abroad</h3>
  <p>
    NHI provides limited coverage for emergency treatment abroad—you can claim reimbursement for overseas emergency care, but at Taiwan rates which are much lower than costs in places like the US. This isn't adequate coverage for living abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>NHI Suspension</h3>
  <p>
    If you're abroad for more than 6 months, your NHI coverage is suspended. You stop paying premiums but also lose coverage. When you return, there's a waiting period before coverage resumes (unless you pay back premiums).
  </p>

  <h3>Maintaining NHI</h3>
  <p>
    You can maintain NHI by returning to Taiwan within 6 months or by continuing to pay premiums while abroad through certain arrangements. This keeps your Taiwan coverage active for visits home.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Taiwanese Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Taiwanese companies (Cathay Life, Fubon, Nan Shan) typically provides limited international coverage. For comprehensive protection abroad, international insurance is necessary.
  </p>

  <h2 id="nhi-considerations">NHI Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Understanding NHI rules helps you plan healthcare abroad:
  </p>

  <h3>6-Month Rule</h3>
  <p>
    If you leave Taiwan for more than 6 consecutive months, NHI suspends. Brief returns to Taiwan can reset this clock. Plan your visits strategically if you want to maintain NHI.
  </p>

  <h3>Reinstatement</h3>
  <p>
    When you return to Taiwan, NHI coverage resumes after a waiting period (typically 3-6 months) unless you pay the premiums for the period you were away. Calculate whether paying back premiums is worthwhile.
  </p>

  <h3>Emergency Reimbursement</h3>
  <p>
    NHI does reimburse some overseas emergency costs, but at Taiwan rates. A US emergency room visit might cost $10,000—NHI might reimburse $500. This gap requires international insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Dual Coverage Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Some Taiwanese expats maintain NHI for Taiwan visits while having international insurance for their residence country. This provides comprehensive global coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Healthcare Quality Expectations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Taiwan's NHI provides excellent care at low cost. International insurance should match your quality expectations—don't settle for basic coverage that would feel like a downgrade from Taiwan's system.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage ideal for Taiwanese expats. Strong US networks are critical—many Taiwanese work in US tech companies. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 service with Mandarin support available. Taiwan coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Taiwanese expats in the US who want reliable coverage with strong networks.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Service quality matches Taiwanese expectations for efficiency and responsiveness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Taiwan coverage available as an add-on.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Taiwanese professionals who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe and adequate coverage elsewhere. Good value for comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Taiwanese expats seeking good value, especially for European destinations.
  </p>

  <h3>Cathay Life</h3>
  <p>
    Cathay Life is Taiwan's largest life insurer and offers international products. Familiar brand, Mandarin service, Taiwan coverage included. International networks are more limited than global specialists.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Taiwanese expats who prefer familiar Taiwanese service with seamless home coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Fubon Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Fubon is a major Taiwanese insurer offering some international products. Familiar service, Taiwan coverage included. International networks are limited compared to global insurers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Taiwanese expats who want familiar service and primarily need Taiwan coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Get quotes from multiple providers. Consider US network strength if that's your destination—tech industry job changes make continuity important."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwanese expats have specific destination patterns:
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Taiwanese professional community, especially in California (Bay Area, Los Angeles) and other tech hubs. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential. Employer insurance is common but ends with employment.
  </p>

  <h3>Japan</h3>
  <p>
    Close ties and significant Taiwanese community. Japanese healthcare covers residents through employment or National Health Insurance. International insurance covers transitions and provides options.
  </p>

  <h3>Europe</h3>
  <p>
    Growing Taiwanese community, especially in Germany and UK. EU countries have public healthcare for legal residents. International insurance supplements public coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>China (Mainland)</h3>
  <p>
    Business connections mean some Taiwanese work in mainland China. Healthcare infrastructure varies by city. International insurance ensures access to quality facilities.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does NHI cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">NHI provides limited emergency reimbursement at Taiwan rates—far below actual costs in most countries. You need international insurance for adequate coverage abroad.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What happens to NHI after 6 months abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">NHI suspends if you're abroad more than 6 consecutive months. Coverage stops, premiums stop. Returning briefly can reset the clock.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Should I maintain NHI while abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Depends on how often you visit Taiwan. Maintaining NHI keeps Taiwan coverage active. International insurance covers your residence country regardless.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about US employer insurance?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">US employer insurance is tied to employment. Tech layoffs can leave you without coverage. International insurance provides continuity through job changes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Cathay or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Cathay offers Taiwanese familiarity and includes Taiwan. Cigna has stronger global networks, especially in the US. Choose based on destination and preferences.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Mandarin support available?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Taiwanese insurers offer full Mandarin service. Cigna and Bupa have Mandarin support through their Asia operations. Confirm availability for your destination.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwanese expats need comprehensive international insurance—NHI doesn't adequately cover overseas healthcare. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for strong US coverage critical for tech workers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium coverage matching Taiwanese service expectations. <strong>Cathay Life</strong> suits those who prefer familiar Taiwanese service with included home coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    Understand NHI rules before leaving. Consider whether to maintain NHI for Taiwan visits while having international insurance for your residence country.
  </p>

</PageShell>
